715447f-c.text:
(1)
5-17 Wwst 126th Street, adjoining and west of the N.W. corner of Fifth Ave. Building shown at Nos. 13-17, is a hall of the Finnish Educational Society. This site was formerly occupied by 3-two story
frame houses.
March 6, 1936.
P. L. Sperr.
(2)
A view of the Finnish Hall (Nos. 13-17), and apartment house
(No. 11) adjoining.
March 6, 1936.
P. L. Sperr.
NO REPRODUCTIONS. Neg R: 4012
(3)
Three brown stone front houses (Nos. 5-7-9), adjoining the Scoville School, which is directly at the N.W. corner proper.
March 6, 1936.
L. Sperr.
